article.headline: Long Beach St. 80, Cal Poly 77
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. (AP) -- Long Beach State guards Kevin Houston and Aaron Nixon combined to score 48 points Thursday as the 49ers remained in first place in the Big West Conference with an 80-77 victory over Cal Poly. Houston had 22 points and eight rebounds and made two free throws with 17.1 seconds left to lift the 49ers (16-6, 7-2) to their third straight victory. Nixon finished with a game-high 26 points, going 5-of-9 from 3-point range. Sterling Byrd, who missed his first three shots from beyond the arc, hit two 3-pointers in the final five minutes and blocked Trae Clark's desperation 3-pointer with 4 seconds remaining to seal the victory. Dominique Ricks added 17 points for Long Beach State. Cal Poly (11-10, 3-5) was led by Matt Hanson's career-high 19 points off the bench. Derek Stockalper added 17 points for the Mustangs.
